 the case of R. Kunjwal, Quantum 3, 184 (2019),\nnone of the graph invariants from the graph-theoretic framework for\nKS-contextuality due to Cabello, Severini, and Winter (the \"CSW framework\",\nPhys. Rev. Lett. 112, 040401 (2014)) are relevant for our noise-robust\nnoncontextuality inequalities.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 5 May 2018 17:00:57 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 11 May 2018 04:18:25 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 7 Jan 2020 12:21:55 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-01-15"}
