nnealed vs. quenched disorder, affects also public\nopinion. Particularly interesting results are obtained for individualistic\nsocieties, in which public opinion is non-monotonic function of $T$, which\nmeans that there is an optimal social temperature for which an agreement in the\nsociety is the highest.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 6 May 2018 08:42:01 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-05-08"}
