\nthe $\\Lambda$CDM compared to the clustering DBI. Finally, with the help of\nspherical collapse parameters we calculated the relative number density of halo\nobjects above a given mass and conclude that the differences between clustering\nand homogeneous DBI models are more pronounced for higher-mass halos at high\nredshift.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 6 May 2018 11:47:08 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 29 Oct 2018 13:14:38 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-10-30"}
